description:
&lt;p&gt;Interested in Moving &amp; Handling?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an opportunity for a keen and motivated individual to join the DHCFT Moving &amp; Handling / Falls Prevention Service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This will be a key role in supporting the delivery of mandatory training and promotion of best practice within clinical areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be involved in delivery of both patient and inanimate load handling training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience of Moving and Handling training would be an advantage; as would a past working knowledge of DIAG. However, training will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will involve travelling across sites within Derbyshire, supporting both in-patient and community teams, and access to a vehicle will be essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If require further information or for an informal chat please contact Lara Hardy,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07789 743327&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lara Hardy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Patient Manual Handling Trainer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;lara.hardy@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 07789 743327&lt;/p&gt;
